y favorite AI maven presents the ultimate explainer on how tools like chatGPT and Claude can make us smarter.</p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Twentysomething-Treatment-Revolutionary-Remedy-Uncertain/dp/1668012294">The Twentysomething Treatment</a> </strong>by <strong>Meg Jay</strong></p><p>With clarity and compassion, a leading clinical psychologist offers powerful insight on what causes&#8212;and cures&#8212;quarterlife crises.</p><p>3.&nbsp; <strong><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Somehow-Thoughts-Love-Anne-Lamott/dp/0593714415">Somehow</a> </strong>by <strong>Anne Lamott</strong></p><p>An eloquent meditation from a beloved author on the process of judging less and caring more.</p><p>4.<strong>&nbsp; <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/aw/d/0593444094/">Says Who?</a> </strong>by <strong>Anne Curzan</strong></p><p>A linguist serves up a guide to using words that will delight everyone who loves language&#8212;and put the grammar police in their place.</p><p>5.<strong>&nbsp; <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Move-Life-Lessons-off-Chessboard/dp/1797223658">Move by Move</a></strong> by <strong>Maurice Ashley</strong></p><p>The chess grandmaster I admire most shares the life lessons from the great game of strategy.</p><p>6.<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/May-Contain-Lies-Statistics-Biases_And/dp/0520405854">May Contain Lies</a> </strong>by <strong>Alex Edmans</strong></p><p>An economist examines how to recognize misinformation, interpret data, and distinguish fact from fiction.</p><p>7.&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Ritual-Effect-Harness-Surprising-Everyday/dp/1982153024">The Ritual Effect</a> </strong>by <strong>Michael Norton</strong></p><p>An eye-opening look from a social psychologist at why we swear by certain routines&#8212;and how we can build more enriching ones.</p><p>8.&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Algebra-Wealth-Formula-Financial-Security/dp/0593714024">The Algebra of Wealth</a> </strong>by <strong>Scott Galloway</strong></p><p>The entrepreneur and marketing guru delivers a financial security playbook that&#8217;s packed with his signature blend of wit and wisdom.</p><p>For a preview of some of these ideas on my podcast:</p><ul><li><p>Ethan Mollick: <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/chatgpt-did-not-title-this-podcast-w-allie-miller-ethan/id1554567118?i=1000605174982">Apple</a> | <a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/4v1ckf6dOEpjBJuwSTmnAa">Spotify</a> | <a href="https://www.ted.com/podcasts/rethinking-with-adam-grant/chatgpt-did-not-title-this-podcast-w-allie-miller-ethan-mollick">Transcript</a></p></li><li><p>Maurice Ashley: <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/chess-grandmaster-maurice-ashley-on-why-mistakes-are/id1554567118?i=1000638596552">Apple</a> | <a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/2ciB1YuXfY8DmVuylaC4Um">Spotify</a> | <a href="https://www.ted.com/podcasts/rethinking-with-adam-grant/chess-grandmaster-maurice-ashley-on-why-mistakes-are-our-greatest-teachers-transcript">Transcript</a></p></li><li><p>Meg Jay and Anne Lamott: coming <a href="https://link.chtbl.com/RTAdam">April 9 and 16</a></p></li></ul>